    "Abstract": "In the quest for efficient inference in machine learning models, especially under resource constraints, we propose a novel framework for Dynamic Geometric Routing (DGR). This approach leverages real-time diagnostics of activation covariance and spectral properties to inform a training-free mechanism for adaptive computational resource allocation. By analyzing the geometric structure of incoming data, we can dynamically adjust the precision of computations, ensuring optimal performance while adhering to strict latency budgets. Our framework builds on the foundational principles of curvature-aware precision routing and aims to replace heuristic fragility claims with formalized stability bounds. We will empirically validate DGR through a series of experiments on single-GPU setups across various benchmarks, measuring throughput-accuracy trade-offs and demonstrating superior performance compared to static allocation methods. This research promises to bridge the gap between theoretical optimization and practical application, providing a transparent, reproducible pathway for scalable inference.",
