proaches. This work aims to bridge the gap between theoretical optimization frameworks and practical, scalable implementations for resource-constrained environments.', 'Experiments': ['1. Implement SLA on a standard convolutional neural network and measure inference latency and accuracy on benchmark datasets (e.g., CIFAR-10, MNIST). Evaluate performance against traditional fixed-layer approaches.', '2. Conduct ablation studies to assess the impact of different spectral decomposition techniques on performance metrics, including layer-skipping frequency and computational savings.', '3. Test SLA under varying input distributions to evaluate its adaptability and robustness compared to baseline models without dynamic adaptations.', '4. Measure the impact of SLA on memory bandwidth usage and compute efficiency, providing comprehensive latency benchmarks.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['Potential sensitivity to noise in activation signals affecting spectral diagnostics.', 'The need for careful calibration of thresholds for layer-skipping, which may vary across different models and tasks.', 'Limited generalization to architectures that do not exhibit low-rank characteristics in their hidden states.']}
