      {
        "Description": "Analyze the stability and generalization performance of models trained with CAPAR.",
        "Method": "Perform multi-seed training and evaluate the variance in validation accuracy. Use PAC-Bayes bounds to quantify generalization performance.",
        "Metrics": "Validation accuracy variance, PAC-Bayes bounds"
      },
      {
        "Description": "Assess the impact of curvature-aware precision adaptation on different layers of the network.",
        "Method": "Monitor the precision levels of individual layers during training and correlate with curvature metrics. Compare with fixed-precision baselines.",
        "Metrics": "Layer-wise precision levels, curvature metrics"
      }
    ],
    "Risk Factors and Limitations": [
      "The effectiveness of curvature-aware precision adaptation may vary across different architectures and datasets.",
      "Deterministic spectral estimators may introduce additional computational overhead, which needs to be carefully managed.",
      "The approach assumes that curvature information is a reliable indicator for precision adaptation, which may not always hold in practice."
    ]
  }
}
